comment.body:
@theta no, don't change the file itself. 

It's a command to execute. I have now updated the above description. 
See the line starting with "python zeronet.py etc."

@musickiller from which page exactly? 

just looked at https://github.com/HelloZeronet/ZeroNet/releases and there are only ZN 0.3.4 and 0.3.5. 
If they take it from the master branch on github it should be newest revision1098 (same would be for ZeroBundle).

@theta you are missing a dependency: python-gevent

Please see on the https://github.com/HelloZeroNet/ZeroNet page for more dependencies you might also miss and need to install.
(I also assume you are not running ZeroBundle, since it should have all dependencies inside.)

@up4 yes, it is a bot, 
and I just looked: 
it sent the reply 2 mins before you posted here. Did you get it?

@voom maybe, but:

it is strange that all 4 went offline at the same time, and still are down. 
Chances if they would belong to >1 person should be higher, that someone notices their proxy is down.

@musickiller
- see "[Distributing on torrent probably would cause other problems,since it's blocked on many networks even outside of China](https://github.com/HelloZeroNet/ZeroNet/issues/416)"
- gateways/proxies: yes, if we can trust the proxy operator. But that problem exists everywhere. We"d need to provide also a strong hash/gpg checksum on the file(s) itself.

@theta you can sign and publish in 2 ways: 
a. in terminal, see [FAQ](http://zeronet.readthedocs.org/en/latest/using_zeronet/create_new_site/) or 
b. via the UI (see pic of hidden menu [here](/zeroblog.bit/?Post:15:get+yourself+an+ID+@+ZeroVerse.bit), search for: "via the hidden menu")
